: Explore iOS Filesystem and Keychain Secrets
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Understand iOS filesystem structure and security mechanisms
Set up simulated iOS environments for security testing on Linux
Extract and analyze keychain data using custom Python tools
Identify security vulnerabilities in iOS application data storage
Generate comprehensive security assessment reports
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command line proficiency
Fundamental Python programming skills
Understanding of mobile application security concepts
Familiarity with file permissions and directory structures
Lab Environment
This lab uses Al Nafi's pre-configured Linux cloud machines. Click Start Lab to access your environment with all necessary tools pre-installed. No additional setup required.

Task 1: Create Simulated iOS Filesystem
Step 1: Set Up Directory Structure
Create a simulated iOS filesystem for security testing:

# Create working directory
mkdir -p ~/ios-security-lab
cd ~/ios-security-lab

# Create iOS filesystem structure
mkdir -p ios-filesystem/{Applications,Library,System,var}
mkdir -p ios-filesystem/Applications/TestApp.app
mkdir -p ios-filesystem/Library/{Keychains,Preferences,Caches}
mkdir -p ios-filesystem/var/{mobile,log}

# Verify structure
tree ios-filesystem/
Step 2: Create Sample Application Files
Generate sample iOS application data:

# Create Info.plist
cat > ios-filesystem/Applications/TestApp.app/Info.plist << 'EOF'
